<HEADLINE>
<P>
WILLIS E. PEQUEGNAT; HEAD OF CLAREMONT ZOOLOGY DEPARTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Willis E. Pequegnat, 79, biologist, ecologist, author and teacher who taught 
for 20 years at Pomona College in Claremont, where he was head of the zoology 
department.He earned his doctorate in zoology in 1942 at UCLA and worked as a 
ranger naturalist at Yosemite National Park before joining Pomona. During the 
summer he taught marine biology at Caltech's laboratory in Corona del Mar. In 
1960 he was named program director at the National Science Foundation, serving 
two years, and then taught in the graduate oceanography program at Texas A & M, 
retiring in 1980. Pequegnat also served as a consultant to governments, oil 
companies and environmental concerns. In La Jolla on April 2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
