<HEADLINE>
<P>
DENNIS DURNEY; ACTOR AND PRODUCER OF TV MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dennis Durney, 60, actor and producer of such television films as "Shadow 
Riders."The son of highly successful screenwriter Dorothy Kingsley, Durney 
worked with his mother on a television remake of "Angels in the Outfield" in 
1991. As an actor, he had roles in the films "Where the Boys Are," "A Ticklish 
Affair" and "Atlantis, the Lost Continent." In 1982, he produced author Louis 
L'Amour's "Shadow Riders" for television, starring Sam Elliott and Tom Selleck. 
His other productions included "Molly and Lawless John," a television movie 
with Vera Miles and Elliott, and "Beretta's Island" with Arnold Schwarzenegger. 
On Wednesday in Los Angeles of heart failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
