<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALEXANDER TO LEAD NEA CONFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The National Endowment for the Arts has issued an open invitation to a 
conference, "ART-21: Art Reaches Into the 21st Century," Thursday through April 
16 at the Hyatt Regency Hotel in Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
 NEA Chairman Jane Alexander will lead the conference, which will address four 
themes: the artist's place in society, the arts and technology, expanding 
resources and lifelong learning. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (800) 632-7821. 
</P>
<P>
 The conference also will be accessible on Arts Wire, a national computer 
network for the arts. 
</P>
<P>
 Information and subscriptions: (212) 366-6900. 
</P>
