</P>
<P>
 A first-time offender, Voss, 62, received the usual sentence for driving under 
the influence, including three years' informal probation and $1,350 in fines 
and court costs. In lieu of 48 hours in jail, a work program was recommended 
for Voss, a customary option. 
</P>
