<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; FATHER IS SUSPECT IN DEATH OF BABY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO ROMERO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have arrested a 28-year-old man in connection with the death of his 
6-month-old daughter. 
</P>
<P>
 The infant, Cathy Licet Ramirez, died at UCI Medical Center in Orange early 
Thursday.Doctors attributed her death to severe blows to the abdomen, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruperto Ramirez, a father of five, was arrested Thursday night at his home in 
the 1600 block of West 3rd Street. 
</P>
<P>
 About 4:15 a.m. Thursday, paramedics and police had been summoned to the home 
on a report that a child needed medical attention, Santa Ana Police Sgt. Dick 
Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 The infant's mother, Catalina Gomez, 27, could not be reached for comment 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 A woman who said she lives with her two small children in the same A-frame 
house as the family said she was shocked that anyone would think Ramirez could 
kill his daughter. 
</P>
<P>
 "All I know is that they treat their five children right," the woman, who 
declined to give her name, said of the couple. "I never saw him or her hit 
their children. (The children) sometimes behave like brats, and she really lets 
them have it, but kill one of them? No. I'm sorry, but that is not true." 
</P>
<P>
 The woman said she did not hear anything unusual in the house the night 
authorities were called. 
</P>
<P>
 Faust said Ramirez was taken to Santa Ana City Jail, where he awaits 
arraignment on a murder charge. His bail was set at $250,000. FERNANDO ROMERO 
</P>
