ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TEMPLE TO HOLD EVENT TO MARK HOLOCAUST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Several hundred members of the Jewish community are expected to observe Yom 
Hashoah, Holocaust Remembrance Day, at Temple Beth Sholom in Santa Ana on 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The ceremony honoring those killed in the Holocaust will be held in the temple 
sanctuary at 2625 N. Tustin Ave.It begins at 2 p.m. and is free and open to the 
public, said Chelle Friedman, spokeswoman for the Jewish Federation of Orange 
County, which is co-sponsoring the event. 
</P>
<P>
 Participating cantors from Orange County synagogues include Yossie Chazan of 
Temple Eliat in Mission Viejo, Judith Myersberg of Temple Beth Sholom, Don 
Croll of Temple Beth David in Westminster, Shula Kalir-Merton of Temple Beth El 
in Aliso Viejo and Linda Ecker of Congregation B'nai Tzedek in Fountain Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The observance is co-sponsored by several groups, including the Orange County 
chapter of the American Jewish Committee, the Anti-Defamation League of B'nai 
B'rith of Orange County, Jewish Educators Assn., Orange County Bureau of Jewish 
Education, Orange County Board of Rabbis and the U.S. Holocaust Memorial 
Council. 
</P>
<P>
 The Child Survivors, Second Generation and Shoah Survivors are also 
co-sponsors in cooperation with the Auschwitz Study Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 259-0655.DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</TEXT>
