<TEXT>
<P>
 Running back Mark Higgs took a pay cut from $810,000 to $450,000 plus 
incentives to remain with the Miami Dolphins, and if linebacker John Offerdahl 
doesn't retire because of injuries, he is leaning toward accepting a similar 
deal because of pressures to get the team under the NFL salary cap. . . . The 
Washington Redskins released defensive end Al Noga and signed free-agent center 
Trevor Matich, formerly of the Indianapolis Colts, to a two-year, $700,000 
contract to be their long snapper. 
</P>
