 With two on and the score tied, 2-2, late in the seventh inning, third baseman 
Robert Echavarria singled in the winning run to give Fullerton a 3-2 victory 
over Buena Park in a Freeway League baseball game Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Schatz tied the score with a double in the beginning of the seventh 
inning. The fifth-ranked Indians remain undefeated in league play (13-2, 5-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In other Freeway League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 8, La Habra 5 -- Joey Gomez hit a two-run double to key a seven-run 
Sonora rally in the second, and he also homered in the fourth for host Sonora 
(7-8, 1-4). Jeremy Payne homered for La Habra (0-5 in league). 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 6, Sunny Hills 2 -- Nic Ruzzi had a single, double and triple and drove 
in four runs for visiting Troy (10-4, 3-2). Kevin Gray (5-2) pitched a 
five-hitter, striking out five for the third-ranked Warriors. 
