ROUNDUP; EL DORADO GETS PAST VALENCIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sean Morrison had 30 kills to lead El Dorado past Valencia, 15-13, 6-15, 
15-11, 16-18, 15-9, in an Empire League volleyball match Friday night at 
Valencia High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Gary Espley and Clint Ward each had 15 kills for the Golden Hawks (6-2, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia (5-4, 1-1) was led by Joe Reynoza, who had 28 kills, and Jason Miele, 
who added 17. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Empire League matches: 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 3, Cypress 0 -- Mike Allison had 16 kills and Jason Klems added 11 
for host Esperanza (6-2, 2-0), which defeated Cypress, 15-11, 15-6, 15-2. 
</P>
