<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: ANDERSON TO COACH MASTER'S WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Susan Anderson, a former All-Southwestern Conference basketball player for the 
University of Texas, has been named women's basketball coach at The Master's 
College.  
</P>
<P>
 Anderson, who has been playing professionally in Brazil and Japan the past two 
years, replaces Cliff McManis, who resigned in March. High School Basketball  
</P>
<P>
 Numerous area high school basketball players are scheduled to participate in a 
Southern California all-star doubleheader tonight at Cal State Los Angeles, 
pitting seniors from Southern Section schools against their counterparts from 
the City Section.  
</P>
<P>
 The girls' game begins at 6 p.m. followed by the boys' at 8. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern Section players include Richard O'Neill of Crescenta Valley, Cody 
Patterson of Hart, Alex Lopez of Campbell Hall, Jason Hartman of Thousand Oaks 
and Ramon Jose of Glendale. Damon Ollie and Fantasia Johnson of North Hollywood 
will represent the City Section. 
</P>
<P>
 John Goffredo, who led Crescenta Valley to the Division I final, will serve as 
Southern Section coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Playing for the Southern Section girls' team will be Sara Hagman of Crescenta 
Valley and Michelle Giordano of Buena. Tamika McThomas of El Camino Real will 
play for the City team. Baseball  
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Bennett, a senior catcher for Newbury Park High, has signed a letter of 
intent to attend Master's. Bennett entered the week batting .317 with one home 
run. Water Polo  
</P>
<P>
 David Block, a junior member of the Westlake High water polo team, has been 
selected to the 15-member U.S. junior national water polo youth team for 
players 17 and under. The team will tour Greece for two weeks in August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
