<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; MCELDERRY, SADDLEBACK WIN GOLF INVITATIONAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Colin McElderry shot a three-under-par 69 at Whispering Palms Golf Club in San 
Diego as Saddleback won the 13-team San Diego Golf Academy Invitational on 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback edged host San Diego Golf Academy, 360-364. McElderry was match 
medalist. Rancho Santiago was third at 369. 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 4, Saddleback 0 -- Kristen Varagne struck out six and gave up 
three hits to lead Orange Coast (22-10-2, 9-2). Stefanie Ritchey had three 
hits, scored once and had one run batted in for the Pirates. Laura Kesterson 
gave up one earned run and struck out three for Saddleback (17-13, 5-6). 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Coast Conference men's swimming: 
</P>
<P>
