<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALTER TO COACH BISHOP AMAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SHEPARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tom Salter, a football assistant at La Puente Bishop Amat High since 1988, has 
been selected as the school's new coach. 
</P>
<P>
 He will be presented to the team Monday afternoon, when his promotion will be 
announced at a news conference at the school."It would be best if I didn't say 
anything until Monday," Salter said Friday. He is in Tucson with the Bishop 
Amat baseball team. 
</P>
<P>
 Salter, 32, replaces Mark Paredes, who resigned two weeks ago to become coach 
at Riverside North. Paredes said he had recommended several of his assistants 
for the job but was unaware of the final decision. 
</P>
<P>
 It is believed Salter is the only candidate interviewed for the job by the 
school's principal, Msgr. Aidan Carroll, who could not be reached Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Salter graduated from Bishop Amat in 1979. He began his coaching career at the 
school in 1980 while attending Whittier College. ERIC SHEPARD 
</P>
</TEXT>
