<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: TAKE OUR INFO HIGHWAY -- PLEASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTHA GROVES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Enough already! PC Magazine, a computer publication, has had about all the 
information highway puns it can take from newspaper and magazine headlines, 
including its own: The Information Highway Needs Traffic Rules.A Toll Collector 
on the Information Highway. Nationwide Data Highway Faces Speed Bump. 
</P>
<P>
 "Who gave it that boring name anyway?" the magazine asked in its April 26 
issue. "Why didn't they call it the Siliconbahn?" 
</P>
<P>
 The publication invited its readers to help rename the whatchamacallit. 
</P>
<P>
 "We'll pick a winner," the magazine said, "and together we'll change the 
course of history." MARTHA GROVES 
</P>
</TEXT>
