</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Space Station Contract: McDonnell Douglas Aerospace of Huntington Beach said 
Friday that it has contracted with Minneapolis-based computer maker Honeywell 
Inc. to build a computerized command and control system for the nation's 
proposed space station. Honeywell will be paid $129 million to design and 
construct the space station's central computer, which would control the 
station's complex electrical system, life support systems and communications 
equipment to transmit data back to Earth. 
