<P>
 Boeing to Design New Fighter: The Seattle-based aircraft company and two 
engine makers will design a new fighter plane in an attempt to win a contract 
to produce the jets for the U.S. Marines and Air Force, Boeing said. Boeing is 
teamed on the $32-million project with Pratt & Whitney and Rolls-Royce.The work 
is being done under an agreement announced with the Defense Department's 
Advanced Research Projects Agency, which is expected to decide in 1996 whether 
to develop a prototype based on one of the designs, Boeing officials said. If 
the go-ahead is given, a prototype probably would not fly before 1999, Boeing 
said. Boeing is to come up with a concept for an advanced short takeoff and 
vertical landing fighter, to compete with designs by Lockheed and McDonnell 
Douglas. 
