<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: NOW CHAPTER BACKS BID TO RECALL ROBERTI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The San Fernando Valley/northeast Los Angeles branch of the National 
Organization for Women has endorsed the recall of state Sen. David A. Roberti, 
citing his record on abortion. 
</P>
<P>
 "There are many reasons we dislike him, primarily his anti-choice stand," said 
Linda McCabe, the chapter's coordinator. 
</P>
<P>
 While the members of NOW have mixed feelings about gun control -- the central 
issue in the Roberti recall campaign -- they are strongly pro-choice. NOW 
believes that the Van Nuys Democrat's record shows him to be an opponent of 
abortion, even though he claims to be a moderate.  
</P>
<P>
 Although the chapter has endorsed the Roberti recall campaign, NOW has refused 
to support any of the candidates vying to replace him for the remainder of his 
term, McCabe said. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</TEXT>
