<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HOSPITALIZED AFTER SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In what may be a gang-related incident, shots fired from one car into another 
in Mission Hills Friday seriously injured a Pacoima man, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Raudel Guardado, 20, remained on life support at Holy Cross Medical Center in 
Mission Hills. Two men in the car with Guardado, who were not hurt, drove him 
to the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said Guardado's car stopped at a stop sign at Fox Street and 
Arleta Avenue when a second car pulled up and the driver fired several shots.  
</P>
<P>
 Police said they do not have a motive for the 12:07 a.m. shooting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
