<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DIES OF GUNSHOT WOUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHAU LAM, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Sherman Oaks man who was found lying on a curb suffering from several 
gunshot wounds died later at a local hospital, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Several residents on the quiet block of 4000 Dixie Canyon Avenue, where 
residents jog and take late night walks, heard shots fired about 12:45 a.m. and 
called police. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities declined to name the 29-year-old man until family members are 
notified. Police said he was alive when paramedics arrived and took him to 
North Hollywood Medical Center where he died. 
</P>
<P>
 Resident Lowell Hoskins said he and his daughter were watching television when 
shots were fired. They heard a car pull away but saw nothing, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have break-ins, but nothing like this before," said Hoskins, who has lived 
in the area for 14 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Caretaker Josephine Koker, who lives near where the body was found, said she 
was awakened by a loud noise and thought it was another earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have no suspects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
