 BEER HISTORY: Who says we are having trade problems with Japan? Certainly 
nobody at the Van Nuys Anheuser-Busch plant, and with good reason. That's 
because the first Japanese beer ever manufactured in the U.S. for large-scale 
sale in Japan rolled off the assembly line Friday. . . . The beer was even 
blessed by a Shinto Priest (B1). 
</P>
