<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; NEW 
GENERAL MANAGER NAMED FOR COLISEUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Spectacor, the facilities manager at the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum and the 
adjacent Sports Arena, this week announced the appointment of its fifth general 
manager for the facilities in the six years it has run them. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Lynch, 37, who has been serving as general manager of the 
Knickerbocker Arena in Albany, N.Y., will replace Jay Hagerman on 
Friday.Hagerman will become general manager of the Mobile Civic Center in 
Mobile, Ala. Coliseum sources said that Hagerman, who is originally from the 
South, had requested the transfer. 
</P>
<P>
 Also leaving the Coliseum-Sports Arena management team is public relations 
spokeswoman Cindy Rubin, who has accepted a position with a South Bay public 
relations firm. A replacement for her will be named shortly, interim spokesman 
Robert Schwartz said. 
</P>
<P>
 Spectacor's managers have had little direct responsibility for the earthquake 
repair work at the Coliseum, which remains under the leadership of the Coliseum 
Commission's project director, Don C. Webb. 
</P>
</TEXT>
