<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; STRIPING 
WORK TO CLOSE FREEWAY CAR-POOL LANES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The car-pool lanes on the quake-damaged Santa Monica Freeway (Interstate 10) 
were scheduled to be closed at midnight Friday so crews can add new traffic 
striping to the highway for its reopening early next week, a Caltrans spokesman 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 The freeway, severed at Fairfax Avenue and La Cienega Boulevard in the Jan. 17 
earthquake, is scheduled to reopen before the rush hour Tuesday, Caltrans 
spokesman Russell Snyder said.Eastbound motorists will have to exit at 
Robertson Boulevard and take surface streets to the La Cienega Boulevard 
on-ramp. Westbound cars must get off the freeway at La Brea Avenue for a detour 
to Washington Boulevard.  
</P>
<P>
 The eastbound La Cienega Boulevard on- and off-ramps will remain closed for 
reconstruction, but all other ramps will be open.  
</P>
<P>
 Although the car-pool lane experiment was successful, Snyder said, the rebuilt 
freeway will not have car-pool lanes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
