<HEADLINE>
<P>
REALIGNMENT: CAN CLASSIC BASEBALL BE FAR BEHIND? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In Sunday's sports section, Ross Newhan quoted Brave General Manager John 
Schuerholz as having endorsed baseball's realignment and playoff structure 
because 54% of fans polled favored it. 
</P>
<P>
 If memory serves me right, this is the same percentage that liked the new 
Coca-Cola better than the old. What Coca-Cola failed to take into account was 
that the 46% who didn't like the new taste switched to something else. 
</P>
<P>
 Can we look forward to "Classic Baseball?" 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID LITTLE 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
