<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MINORS; CROWD CHEERS, BUT JORDAN GOES 
0-FOR-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Jordan went 0-for-3 with two swinging strikeouts and a weak fly ball 
Friday night in his pro baseball debut for the Double-A Birmingham Barons, who 
lost, 10-3, to Chattanooga in Hoover, Ala. 
</P>
<P>
 "They told me you sometimes have nights like this," Jordan said. "I was a 
little eager to try to get a base hit and try to start off right. 
</P>
<P>
 "I hope I'm not judged on one night. I had games like this in basketball. The 
key is to bounce back." 
</P>
