<TEXT>
<P>
 Wrong Foundation -- The National Health Foundation referred to in a story in 
the Valley Edition of the Los Angeles Times on April 1 is not the National 
Health Foundation based in Los Angeles. The former was cited in a lawsuit by 
the U.S. Department of Labor as part of a health-care plan that allegedly 
bilked contributors out of $1.1 million. The Los Angeles-based NHF, a nonprofit 
organization located at 201 N. Figueroa St., is not associated with the 
American Healthcare Underwriting Managers, Inc., and has not been accused of 
any wrongdoing. 
</P>
