<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; FAMILY CHANNEL REVIVES 'HOLOCAUST' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In observance of Holocaust Remembrance Week, the Family Channel revives the 
1978 miniseries "Holocaust," starring James Woods, Meryl Streep and Michael 
Moriarty. The five-part drama won eight Emmy Awards. It begins Sunday at 8 p.m. 
and continues nightly through Thursday. N.F. MENDOZA 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
